Go! Go!

668
00:55:08,179 --> 00:55:09,476
Eddie.

669
00:55:11,549 --> 00:55:13,380
Melissa.

670
00:55:20,624 --> 00:55:21,921
Hey.

671
00:55:25,830 --> 00:55:29,129
Don't tell me I look good,
'cause I know.

672
00:55:31,102 --> 00:55:33,093
I didn't want you to see me this way.

673
00:55:33,704 --> 00:55:35,569
You look good.

674
00:55:35,639 --> 00:55:38,369
Oh, I, uh...

675
00:55:38,442 --> 00:55:40,467
Yeah, I sorta got myself together.

676
00:55:40,544 --> 00:55:43,035
NZT will do that to you.

677
00:55:43,114 --> 00:55:46,015
- What do you mean?
- I mean, I took it, too.

678
00:55:46,984 --> 00:55:49,748
Vernon didn't tell you
any of this, did he?

679
00:55:49,820 --> 00:55:50,912
No.

680
00:55:50,988 --> 00:55:52,717
Well, when he told me
about this amazing new drug,

681
00:55:52,790 --> 00:55:56,749
I was like, down the hatch.
And it was. It was amazing.

682
00:55:56,827 --> 00:56:00,490
I read Brian Greene's
<i>The Elegant Universe</i> in 45 minutes

683
00:56:00,564 --> 00:56:02,429
and I understood it.

684
00:56:02,500 --> 00:56:04,798
My work rate increased
just insanely overnight

685
00:56:04,869 --> 00:56:06,564
and my boss started to hate me.

686
00:56:08,372 --> 00:56:13,275
They offered me his job and then...
and then I got scared.

687
00:56:14,178 --> 00:56:16,442
- Why?
- Why? Because I'm not stupid.

688
00:56:16,514 --> 00:56:19,779
Nobody can operate at that level
of mental activity and not crash.

689
00:56:22,620 --> 00:56:24,485
I stopped taking it.

690
00:56:24,555 --> 00:56:28,924
- And?
- And I got sick. Headaches.

691
00:56:28,993 --> 00:56:34,329
Throwing up.
So I went back to Vernon.

692
00:56:34,398 --> 00:56:36,889
He told me about all the people
that were dying.

693
00:56:38,202 --> 00:56:40,170
How much have you
been taking, Eddie?

694
00:56:40,237 --> 00:56:41,898
I've been taking a lot.

695
00:56:43,507 --> 00:56:47,910
Well, maybe... maybe they've
worked out the bugs. Maybe...

696
00:56:48,779 --> 00:56:50,371
Maybe this is a different batch.

697
00:56:51,816 --> 00:56:54,649
- Yeah.
- You're off it right now, aren't you?

698
00:56:54,718 --> 00:56:57,209
- Just finish your story.
- Well...

699
00:56:57,288 --> 00:57:00,155
...I didn't take any more
and I didn't die.

700
00:57:01,492 --> 00:57:04,586
But after a while, I realized I
couldn't concentrate on anything

701
00:57:04,662 --> 00:57:05,856
for longer than ten minutes.

702
00:57:05,930 --> 00:57:11,027
I, uh... I missed deadlines,
got lazy, slow, so slow.

703
00:57:11,735 --> 00:57:14,203
That was two years ago.

704
00:57:16,140 --> 00:57:18,199
And I haven't been the same since.

705
00:57:22,913 --> 00:57:26,815
Do you have some left? Good.

706
00:57:26,884 --> 00:57:30,251
You go home and you take it. You take
the dose down, but you don't just stop.

707
00:57:30,321 --> 00:57:32,084
You'll die if you just stop.

708
00:57:32,723 --> 00:57:37,524
Try to taper off, otherwise
the headaches are just the beginning.

709
00:57:39,697 --> 00:57:41,062
I have to go.

710
00:57:42,967 --> 00:57:45,527
- Do you know who makes it?
- I don't know.

711
00:57:47,104 --> 00:57:48,571
I have to go.

712
00:58:19,270 --> 00:58:24,071
Oh, shit. Listen, listen, listen.
Listen, listen, listen... OK.

713
00:58:24,141 --> 00:58:25,870
- You forget about me, huh?
- No, no, no, no.

714
00:58:25,943 --> 00:58:27,911
12:00 and you're not here.

715
00:58:27,978 --> 00:58:30,970
- I'm here now. Oh!
- Good.

716
00:58:31,649 --> 00:58:34,277
- Come on, get going.
- I could write you a check.

717
00:58:34,351 --> 00:58:39,345
Check. Check.
Are you out of your mind?

718
00:58:39,423 --> 00:58:41,687
What do you think I am?
Some financial institution?

719
00:58:41,759 --> 00:58:43,852
All right. You're right.
Look, we just need to go to a bank...

720
00:58:48,399 --> 00:58:50,799
What do you got there?

721
00:58:55,105 --> 00:58:57,505
- What is it?
- No, it's just aspirin.

722
00:58:57,574 --> 00:59:03,069
Don't look like no aspirin I ever see.
It's something good, huh?

723
00:59:21,865 --> 00:59:25,995
I feel good, man.
What's in this stuff?

724
00:59:26,070 --> 00:59:28,868
It's just, uh, vitamins and aspirin.

725
00:59:28,939 --> 00:59:32,670
You full of shit, Eddie baby.

726
00:59:58,202 --> 01:00:01,194
Lindy. I wouldn't
have let him in, but...

727
01:00:01,271 --> 01:00:04,001
I'm sorry... Tyler, I gotta go.

728
01:00:05,209 --> 01:00:06,870
I'm sick.

729
01:00:08,412 --> 01:00:12,280
I shouldn't... I'm sorry.
I couldn't make it home.

730
01:00:12,349 --> 01:00:15,443
- Let's get you to a hospital.
- No, no, no, no, no. I don't need...

731
01:00:15,519 --> 01:00:16,577
I need you to get...

732
01:00:16,653 --> 01:00:20,646
It's really simple, babe.
I need my pills.

733
01:00:20,724 --> 01:00:23,318
- Eddie, what pills?
- I don't... Babe, it's complicated.

734
01:00:23,394 --> 01:00:26,158
What are you taking?
Are you on drugs?

735
01:00:26,230 --> 01:00:29,199
They're... it's...

736
01:00:29,266 --> 01:00:32,565
<i>I had no choice.</i>
<i>I told Lindy everything.</i>

737
01:00:34,271 --> 01:00:38,674
So all this energy of yours,
all this focus...

738
01:00:38,742 --> 01:00:40,073
...has been a drug.

739
01:00:40,144 --> 01:00:42,510
Well, it was supposed to be legal.

740
01:00:42,579 --> 01:00:46,174
I have a... a supply stashed.

741
01:00:47,951 --> 01:00:49,714
You want me to go get it.

742
01:00:49,787 --> 01:00:53,245
- No. No, no, no. I'm gonna go get it.
- Give me your keys.

743
01:00:53,323 --> 01:00:54,984
I'll go to your apartment.

744
01:00:55,059 --> 01:00:58,961
It's not... in my apartment.
I moved it.

745
01:00:59,029 --> 01:01:02,829
OK, so where did you move it?

746
01:01:09,562 --> 01:01:11,462
In my house.

747
01:01:13,076 --> 01:01:14,509
Unbelievable.

748
01:01:26,604 --> 01:01:29,368
Hey, have you got it?

749
01:01:29,440 --> 01:01:30,998
Yeah.

750
01:01:33,077 --> 01:01:34,601
There's someone following me.

751
01:01:36,180 --> 01:01:37,408
Are you sure?

752
01:01:37,482 --> 01:01:39,950
Yeah. He got into the cab behind me

753
01:01:40,018 --> 01:01:42,043
and he's making every turn I'm making.

754
01:01:42,120 --> 01:01:45,954
- Baby, call the cops.
- Can you go around him?

755
01:01:46,024 --> 01:01:47,321
<i>Babe, what's happening?</i>

756
01:01:47,392 --> 01:01:49,155
We're stopped dead.

757
01:01:50,461 --> 01:01:52,861
He's getting out.

758
01:01:52,931 --> 01:01:55,525
Eddie, he's walking over here.

759
01:01:55,600 --> 01:01:56,897
Lindy?

760
01:01:57,468 --> 01:01:58,526
Oh, God!

761
01:02:00,405 --> 01:02:01,531
Ow!

762
01:02:13,651 --> 01:02:16,643
Help! Help!

763
01:02:18,256 --> 01:02:20,850
This man's...
This man's chasing me!

764
01:02:20,925 --> 01:02:24,452
He followed me from
my building. I don't know him.

765
01:02:24,529 --> 01:02:27,930
- Please!
- Yo, buddy, let's leave her alone!

766
01:02:30,435 --> 01:02:32,596
Are you deaf?
I said leave her alone.

767
01:02:34,706 --> 01:02:36,799
Hey, buddy, are you
trying to piss me off?

768
01:02:38,610 --> 01:02:40,840
What are you doing, man?

769
01:03:12,396 --> 01:03:15,331
- Are you still there?
- Yeah, I'm here. What happened?

770
01:03:15,399 --> 01:03:18,562
I'm stuck. He'll find me.

771
01:03:18,636 --> 01:03:20,627
<i>OK, stop talking. Don't move.</i>

772
01:03:20,705 --> 01:03:23,367
<i>- He killed two guys.</i>
- What?

773
01:03:23,441 --> 01:03:26,672
- He's gonna kill me, too.
- No, no, no...

774
01:03:26,744 --> 01:03:27,870
Can he see you?

775
01:03:31,582 --> 01:03:33,106
No.

776
01:03:34,318 --> 01:03:35,683
Not yet.

777
01:03:37,054 --> 01:03:39,614
I don't know what to do.

778
01:03:39,690 --> 01:03:43,387
OK, I need you to go into the bag
and take one of the pills.

779
01:03:44,228 --> 01:03:45,525
Why?

780
01:03:45,596 --> 01:03:48,030
<i>Because you'll know what to do.</i>
<i>You'll take it and then you'll know.</i>

781
01:03:48,099 --> 01:03:52,001
He's got a knife. Eddie, I can't
think my way out of a knife.

782
01:03:53,204 --> 01:03:55,297
Just listen to me.
It'll come on in 30 seconds.

783
01:03:55,373 --> 01:03:57,273
And you'll think your way out.
That's what it does.

784
01:04:20,765 --> 01:04:24,360
He's getting closer.

785
01:04:27,004 --> 01:04:28,471
Lindy, I love you.

786
01:05:00,171 --> 01:05:02,105
Hey!

787
01:05:39,810 --> 01:05:41,402
Now turn to me...

788
01:05:43,214 --> 01:05:44,943
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

789
01:05:46,751 --> 01:05:49,311
- Ah!
- Daddy!

790
01:05:49,386 --> 01:05:50,944
Ah!

791
01:05:59,663 --> 01:06:01,255
Eddie. Here.

792
01:06:02,366 --> 01:06:04,459
It's gonna be OK.

793
01:06:06,771 --> 01:06:10,229
We've got to get out of here. Eddie?

794
01:06:45,079 --> 01:06:46,444
You OK?

795
01:06:47,915 --> 01:06:49,712
Yeah.

796
01:06:51,586 --> 01:06:54,919
I'm so sorry about what happened.

797
01:06:54,989 --> 01:06:58,117
I want you to know that you never,
ever have to go through that again,

798
01:06:58,192 --> 01:07:00,956
'cause I can take care of us now.

799
01:07:01,028 --> 01:07:03,053
I'm sure you can.

800
01:07:03,130 --> 01:07:05,655
I can make us safe.
I'm back, OK?

801
01:07:09,937 --> 01:07:12,235
- Who's back, Eddie?
- Me.

802
01:07:12,306 --> 01:07:14,740
No. It's not you.

803
01:07:14,809 --> 01:07:18,404
- You were different before.
- I'm still the same person, Lin.

804
01:07:18,479 --> 01:07:20,106
I wasn't, when I was on it.

805
01:07:21,315 --> 01:07:23,476
I did things I would never do.

806
01:07:23,551 --> 01:07:26,145
- Those things saved your life.
- But they weren't me.

807
01:07:26,220 --> 01:07:27,778
Yes, they were.
No, the way it works...

808
01:07:27,855 --> 01:07:30,323
I know how it works. I get it.

809
01:07:30,391 --> 01:07:33,155
I totally get it.
You feel invincible.

810
01:07:34,428 --> 01:07:37,090
Where it will take us, Lin,
you can't even imagine.

811
01:07:37,164 --> 01:07:41,624
The things we'll be able to do.
Where we'll be a year from now.

812
01:07:41,702 --> 01:07:45,365
The kind of life that
we'll finally be able to live.

813
01:07:45,439 --> 01:07:48,636
Well, you might have
to live it without me.

814
01:07:52,680 --> 01:07:55,342
Look, I am gonna stop taking it.
There's just some things I have to do

815
01:07:55,416 --> 01:07:58,943
to keep us safe and that... To set us up
and then I'm gonna get off it.

816
01:07:59,020 --> 01:08:00,647
- I mean, that's the plan.
- Eddie...

817
01:08:00,721 --> 01:08:03,019
Look, I have a plan. I swear.

818
01:08:03,090 --> 01:08:04,887
I'm gonna get off it.

819
01:08:06,327 --> 01:08:07,658
OK.

820
01:08:09,630 --> 01:08:11,188
I hope you do.

821
01:08:43,397 --> 01:08:45,297
Looking for me?

822
01:08:47,668 --> 01:08:51,331
You think you can run out on me, huh?
You think I don't know where you are?

823
01:08:51,405 --> 01:08:53,202
I was under the impression
our business was settled.

824
01:08:53,274 --> 01:08:55,071
I want some more of that stuff.

825
01:08:55,142 --> 01:08:58,111
Or I shoot you right here.
Take your pick.

826
01:08:58,179 --> 01:08:59,976
<i>This guy was not going away.</i>

827
01:09:00,047 --> 01:09:01,810
<i>A few pills would buy me some time.</i>

828
01:09:01,882 --> 01:09:05,283
- There it is. We're done.
- Oh, yeah. We'll see.

829
01:09:05,353 --> 01:09:07,947
<i>Until I found a more...</i>
<i>permanent solution.</i>

830
01:09:08,623 --> 01:09:12,491
Unless you see a real threat, I never
want it known that I have any security.

831
01:09:12,560 --> 01:09:14,790
You'll never precede me,
you'll always follow me.

832
01:09:14,862 --> 01:09:18,320
Never more than 15 steps behind.
And never stand too close together.

833
01:09:18,399 --> 01:09:21,095
I want to able to look behind me
if the opportunity presents itself.

834
01:09:22,536 --> 01:09:24,800
And don't wear the same color suit.
This isn't <i>The Matrix.</i>

835
01:09:30,544 --> 01:09:32,705
You have to know, Eddie,
I wrote you off.

836
01:09:32,780 --> 01:09:34,441
- I was sick.
- You don't get sick.

837
01:09:34,515 --> 01:09:37,245
You're playing at this level, you get
hit by a car, you don't even die.

838
01:09:37,318 --> 01:09:39,980
- You're absolutely right.
- I know I'm right.

839
01:09:40,054 --> 01:09:41,954
I mean, I didn't know who or what
I was talking to.

840
01:09:42,023 --> 01:09:45,254
A hundred and five. That's who
you were talking to, Carl. Delirium.

841
01:09:45,326 --> 01:09:47,851
Mm-hm.

842
01:09:47,928 --> 01:09:49,225
I sent over my revised projections.

843
01:09:50,231 --> 01:09:51,198
I didn't ask for your projections.

844
01:09:51,265 --> 01:09:53,358
I know, but I think if
you take a look at them...

845
01:09:54,302 --> 01:09:56,133
I already have.
As a matter of fact...

846
01:09:57,705 --> 01:10:00,902
...I fired a few people
over your projections.

847
01:10:00,975 --> 01:10:02,602
- I'm sorry.
- No, you're not.

848
01:10:02,677 --> 01:10:05,510
You're relieved that you know things
my team missed.

849
01:10:05,579 --> 01:10:10,107
The minute,
the instant that's no longer true...

850
01:10:13,020 --> 01:10:14,612
<i>Two months after I'd started NZT,</i>

851
01:10:14,689 --> 01:10:17,817
<i>I was brokering the biggest merger</i>
<i>in corporate history.</i>

852
01:10:17,892 --> 01:10:22,329
Ironically, it's gonna be crude. Crude
is gonna be where we're gonna hit them.

853
01:10:22,396 --> 01:10:25,024
Which yields a prospective profit
of 200 percent.

854
01:10:25,099 --> 01:10:26,964
That makes both of us
very happy campers.

855
01:10:27,034 --> 01:10:29,434
<i>I found that if</i>
<i>I maintained an even dose,</i>

856
01:10:29,503 --> 01:10:31,869
<i>remembered to eat,</i>
<i>drank no alcohol,</i>

857
01:10:31,939 --> 01:10:34,339
<i>- the blackouts didn't recur.</i>
- How you doing, Eddie?

858
01:10:35,309 --> 01:10:38,278
Tom, is it possible to construct
an imperceptible compartment?

859
01:10:38,346 --> 01:10:39,813
In this jacket?

860
01:10:39,880 --> 01:10:43,316
- In all of them.
- Certainly, sir.

861
01:10:43,384 --> 01:10:47,514
<i>Safer though my stash now was, I</i>
<i>was not sitting around until it ran out.</i>

862
01:10:47,588 --> 01:10:50,921
Can I combine these ingredients
in the same exact quantity, yes, but,

863
01:10:50,991 --> 01:10:55,792
the exact method of delivery
to the brain... Darts at a dartboard.

864
01:10:55,863 --> 01:10:58,491
- Meaning?
- Clinical trials, guinea pig people.

865
01:10:58,566 --> 01:11:01,091
- That's gonna take too long.
- It's what it is.

866
01:11:01,168 --> 01:11:04,660
Or you'll kill people.
You need 12, to 18 months...

867
01:11:04,739 --> 01:11:06,866
I'll give you two million dollars
if you can do it in six.

868
01:11:15,416 --> 01:11:19,352
I found that we can cut costs
30 percent and, um...

869
01:11:22,757 --> 01:11:24,088
Excuse me one second.

870
01:11:27,628 --> 01:11:29,823
I thought we straightened this out,
Detective.

871
01:11:29,897 --> 01:11:33,833
This isn't about Vernon Gant,
Mr. Morra.

872
01:11:33,901 --> 01:11:36,301
What is this about?

873
01:11:36,370 --> 01:11:41,706
The witness identified the Maria Winberg
suspect as this person.

874
01:11:46,380 --> 01:11:49,281
Wanna tell me your whereabouts
the night of April 2nd?

875
01:11:50,852 --> 01:11:53,047
<i>I couldn't keep</i>
<i>this quiet on my own.</i>

876
01:11:54,222 --> 01:11:58,750
<i>Enter Morris Brandt...</i>
<i>the most lethal lawyer in New York.</i>

877
01:12:01,763 --> 01:12:06,427
You're lucky somebody wiped the room.
It's weak. Circumstantial at best.

878
01:12:06,501 --> 01:12:09,527
Just between us, were you there?

879
01:12:09,604 --> 01:12:10,832
I don't remember.

880
01:12:12,373 --> 01:12:13,965
I don't want to
make concessions to you...

881
01:12:14,042 --> 01:12:16,101
<i>Carl Van Loon and Hank Atwood</i>

882
01:12:16,177 --> 01:12:20,170
<i>had no idea I might</i>
<i>soon be charged with murder.</i>

883
01:12:20,248 --> 01:12:22,944
But SyCorps, Andine
and others are jockeying

884
01:12:23,017 --> 01:12:25,042
for the same industrial
concessions in Libya

885
01:12:25,119 --> 01:12:27,383
that both our companies are
pretending we're not sniffing out.

886
01:12:27,455 --> 01:12:28,820
How do you know this?

887
01:12:29,824 --> 01:12:32,486
The governmental bribe system
is itself corrupt, so, of course,

888
01:12:32,560 --> 01:12:35,688
information about its inner workings,
like anything, can be bought.

889
01:12:38,266 --> 01:12:39,665
Go on.

890
01:12:39,734 --> 01:12:43,135
If you take a look at the lower
left-hand column, in 2008,

891
01:12:43,204 --> 01:12:46,640
five companies were jockeying for a
position before we even took notice.

892
01:12:50,011 --> 01:12:51,706
Jesus, he looks frail.

893
01:12:52,747 --> 01:12:55,113
- Could be an act.
- He's not even 60.

894
01:12:57,452 --> 01:13:00,512
So, have you decided, Eddie?
What are you gonna do?

895
01:13:00,588 --> 01:13:03,682
When this is over? I don't know.

896
01:13:03,758 --> 01:13:05,157
You haven't given me the answer.

897
01:13:05,226 --> 01:13:07,091
You haven't asked the question.

898
01:13:07,161 --> 01:13:08,924
Well, given the scale
of my contribution,

899
01:13:08,996 --> 01:13:11,328
let's say 45.

900
01:13:11,399 --> 01:13:14,391
Done. Forty-five thousand dollars.

901
01:13:14,469 --> 01:13:17,905
Forty million is plenty, Eddie.
There's a lot more where that came from.

902
01:13:17,972 --> 01:13:20,304
You know, Eddie...

903
01:13:20,374 --> 01:13:21,432
