01:33:40,110 --> 01:33:43,341
Yeah. I bought Eiben a couple of months
ago. I'm surprised you didn't hear.

1130
01:33:43,414 --> 01:33:47,475
No. No. Well, they really
keep me hopping here.

1131
01:33:47,551 --> 01:33:50,349
Well, it's gonna pay off,
Senator Morra.

1132
01:33:51,688 --> 01:33:54,088
The Senate. Who knows...

1133
01:33:54,158 --> 01:33:57,491
Everything's a technicality
from here on in, isn't it, Eddie?

1134
01:33:58,162 --> 01:34:02,724
I think we both know where it's headed,
if you can maintain.

1135
01:34:05,569 --> 01:34:08,766
Have you asked yourself what
you're gonna do when you run out?

1136
01:34:24,488 --> 01:34:27,480
- When did you know?
- Does it matter? I know now.

1137
01:34:28,559 --> 01:34:31,995
I wish you'd come to me at first, Eddie.
I could have bought Eiben at 33 a share.

1138
01:34:32,062 --> 01:34:33,495
We could have been partners.

1139
01:34:37,234 --> 01:34:39,099
So, Eiben makes NZT.

1140
01:34:39,169 --> 01:34:41,967
Well, it'll never officially exist.

1141
01:34:42,039 --> 01:34:44,564
Obviously, I don't need
to point out the advantages for you.

1142
01:34:45,509 --> 01:34:46,999
Oh, I think maybe you do.

1143
01:34:47,077 --> 01:34:51,013
Limitless supply.
We know you can't get any more.

1144
01:34:51,081 --> 01:34:52,605
You sure about that?

1145
01:34:52,683 --> 01:34:54,480
They shut down your lab this morning.

1146
01:34:57,020 --> 01:35:00,547
Eddie. I just want to help you,
that's all.

1147
01:35:00,624 --> 01:35:03,616
Keep you supplied.
No disruption in service.

1148
01:35:03,694 --> 01:35:05,753
Give you peace of mind.
That's all.

1149
01:35:07,431 --> 01:35:10,423
And in return, I do what?

1150
01:35:10,501 --> 01:35:14,335
Get a little advice, maybe.
I won't be bothering you much at first.

1151
01:35:14,404 --> 01:35:16,872
And later. What are you
gonna be bothering me with?

1152
01:35:16,940 --> 01:35:20,637
Well, given where you're heading,
some of our ideas are a bit ambitious.

1153
01:35:20,711 --> 01:35:22,576
But hey, I think they're achievable.

1154
01:35:22,646 --> 01:35:24,409
And what if I don't like your ideas?

1155
01:35:24,481 --> 01:35:26,881
Then we'll say, "Godspeed."

1156
01:35:26,950 --> 01:35:30,442
And your candle will have shed a brief,
but lovely light.

1157
01:35:32,322 --> 01:35:33,812
But you know what, Eddie,
let's not even

1158
01:35:33,891 --> 01:35:34,880
go there right now.

1159
01:35:34,958 --> 01:35:38,257
Right now, I just want
to keep you brilliant...

1160
01:35:38,328 --> 01:35:42,059
...and healthy. Come on.
Let's go get some lunch.

1161
01:36:00,317 --> 01:36:02,285
After you, Senator.

1162
01:36:03,820 --> 01:36:05,720
Thanks for stopping by, Carl.

1163
01:36:06,623 --> 01:36:08,386
Give us a second.

1164
01:36:08,458 --> 01:36:11,154
What are you doing? Do you want
to be President of the United States

1165
01:36:11,228 --> 01:36:13,924
- or brain dead, stuck full of tubes?
- I'll take my chances.

1166
01:36:13,997 --> 01:36:17,228
I told you your chances don't exist.
We shut down your lab.

1167
01:36:17,301 --> 01:36:18,495
You don't think some smartass on NZT

1168
01:36:18,569 --> 01:36:20,196
might have two or three
or even four labs?

1169
01:36:20,270 --> 01:36:22,431
- So what? You're not making any more.
- That's right, I'm not.

1170
01:36:22,506 --> 01:36:24,565
I thought better of it.
See, once you know what's in it,

1171
01:36:24,641 --> 01:36:28,270
you can tweak it, re-engineer it.
Get the bugs out. Taper off.

1172
01:36:28,979 --> 01:36:30,310
I'm off it, Carl.

1173
01:36:30,380 --> 01:36:31,642
Well, on it or off it,

1174
01:36:31,715 --> 01:36:34,013
there's no scenario
where you're not working for me.

1175
01:36:34,084 --> 01:36:35,608
How you gonna pay me?
In cigarettes?

1176
01:36:35,686 --> 01:36:36,846
Last year you traded

1177
01:36:36,920 --> 01:36:38,888
- inside information 17 times.
- You threatening me?

1178
01:36:38,956 --> 01:36:42,016
Blank checks from Dubai.
Dumping in Chile. Disappeared officials.

1179
01:36:42,092 --> 01:36:44,185
- I mean, you shed a spot light...
- Do you want to go to war with me?

1180
01:36:44,261 --> 01:36:46,388
And trust me when I say this,
I'm not even being creative.

1181
01:36:46,463 --> 01:36:48,431
There's no way you can be making
accusations like that

1182
01:36:48,498 --> 01:36:50,830
and be walking around alive.

1183
01:36:50,901 --> 01:36:53,495
That you would even think that shows me
how unprepared you are to fight me.

1184
01:36:53,570 --> 01:36:55,128
- You're no longer equipped to fight me.
- I may be off it,

1185
01:36:55,205 --> 01:36:57,605
but you think I didn't learn anything?
That my synapses didn't change?

1186
01:36:57,674 --> 01:36:59,005
That I kept absolutely nothing?

1187
01:36:59,076 --> 01:37:00,668
You have no idea what
kind of enemy I can be.

1188
01:37:00,744 --> 01:37:03,611
- That van's gonna rear-end that taxi.
- What?

1189
01:37:03,680 --> 01:37:06,342
The driver's distracted. He's texting.
He's going 30 miles an hour.

1190
01:37:06,416 --> 01:37:08,213
He has 60 feet to stop.
He doesn't have room.

1191
01:37:08,285 --> 01:37:10,082
What van?

1192
01:37:13,390 --> 01:37:14,789
I see everything, Carl.

1193
01:37:14,858 --> 01:37:17,156
I'm 50 moves ahead of you
and everybody else.

1194
01:37:17,227 --> 01:37:19,559
What makes you think I don't have a guy
with a bead on you right now?

1195
01:37:19,630 --> 01:37:21,359
How do you know you're gonna be alive
this time next year?

1196
01:37:21,431 --> 01:37:24,594
What are you doing? You get
your hands off me. What are you doing?

1197
01:37:24,668 --> 01:37:27,432
Something's pumping half-mass in there.
The walls of your heart are dilated.

1198
01:37:27,504 --> 01:37:30,701
Your aortic valve's steno. So you're
gonna need to get that replaced.

1199
01:37:32,476 --> 01:37:34,103
But you already knew that.

1200
01:37:39,916 --> 01:37:41,781
You know, you should
really be glad about this.

1201
01:37:41,852 --> 01:37:44,878
'Cause me working for you?
You'd end up as my bitch.

1202
01:37:56,833 --> 01:37:59,597
Maybe we should cool off.
Talk again.

1203
01:38:01,438 --> 01:38:03,303
I don't think so.

1204
01:38:04,908 --> 01:38:06,136
Don't forget to vote.

1205
01:38:14,451 --> 01:38:15,884
Edward.

1206
01:38:15,952 --> 01:38:17,579
You good?

1207
01:38:17,654 --> 01:38:20,623
Yeah. Told you I have a lunch.

1208
01:38:26,563 --> 01:38:28,929
- Sorry I'm late.
- Hey. Don't worry.

1209
01:38:31,001 --> 01:38:33,526
- How's your day going?
- Ah. I've had better.

1210
01:38:35,405 --> 01:38:37,396
I still can't deal with that haircut.

1211
01:38:37,474 --> 01:38:39,567
I wouldn't even
recognize you on the street.

1212
01:38:39,643 --> 01:38:41,406
Well, I'm a new man.

1213
01:38:42,713 --> 01:38:43,737
I've already ordered.

1214
01:38:59,663 --> 01:39:01,324
What?

1215
01:45:31,421 --> 01:45:32,410
ENGLISH US

